            "title": "Global FMCG sales expected to reach USD6.6 trillion by year-end, growing by 4.6% in 2025 due to price-led value gains.",
            "id": "9059854c-4e85-4d74-afde-e8222aeaa516",
            "description": "In London, the FMCG market is projected to see a 4.6% growth by the conclusion of 2025, as per data analysis firm Euromonitor International. This growth is anticipated despite persistent financial worries and the burden of living costs. The increase in the market is primarily propelled by value gains led by pricing strategies. Consumer behavior is significantly influenced by price sensitivity, which remains a key factor even with the alleviation of inflationary pressures. Consumers are actively seeking enhanced value propositions, including private label goods, budget-friendly stores, and loyalty programs. These insights are based on the latest data analytics on FMCG trends.",
